SIMPLE: gyve
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gyve
<hw>Gyve</hw> <pr>(j⟦imac⟧v)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of Celtic origin;
cf. W. <ets>gefyn</ets>, Ir. <ets>geibhionn</ets>, Gael.
<ets>geimheal</ets>.]</ety> <def>A shackle; especially, one to confine
the legs; a fetter.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>give</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Like a poor prisoner in his twisted <qex>gyves</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With <qex>gyves</qex> upon his wrist.</q>
<rj><qau>Hood.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gyve</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gyve
<hw>Gyve</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<er>Gyved</er> <pr>(j⟦imac⟧vd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<er>Gyving</er>.]</vmorph> <def>To fetter; to shackle; to chain.</def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will <qex>gyve</qex> thee in thine own courtship.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>


